            <LEXSense LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="2022-02-09 12:44:43" LastEditedBy="">
              <DefinitionLong/>
              <DefinitionShort>the flesh of both animals and human beings</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>flesh</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>Some languages make an important distinction between the flesh of a living person and the flesh of someone who has been killed or who has died. It would be this latter sense which should be reflected in {S:06601901800040}. In {S:04500202800030} the reference to ‘circumcision in the flesh’ (ἐν σαρκὶ περιτομή) would, however, require the first sense, namely, the flesh of a living person.</Comments>
